column1: # Supplemental File S2 - Sheffield Nanopore Noncanonical Sub-Genomic RNA Counts
# Noncanonical sub-genomic counts for the Sheffield Nanopore dataset from clinical SARS-CoV-2 samples
# pos: genomic position of leader-genome junction
# amplicons: The amplicon(s) that gave rise to the sub-genomic RNA
# gRNA_count: The number of genomic reads at this ORF
# nsgRNA_HQ_count: The number of high quality reads supporting noncanonical sub-genomic RNA at this position
# nsgRNA_LQ_count: The number of low quality reads supporting noncanonical sub-genomic RNA at this position
# nsgRNA_LLQ_count: The number of low low quality reads supporting noncanonical sub-genomic RNA at this position
# gRHPT: Genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
# nsgRPTg_HQ: High quality noncanonical sub-genomic reads per thousand genomic
# nsgRPTg_LQ: Low quality noncanonical sub-genomic reads per thousand genomic
# nsgRPTg_LLQ: Low low quality noncanonical sub-genomic reads per thousand genomic
# nsgRPTg_ALL: All noncanonical noncanonical sub-genomic reads per thousand genomic
# nsgRPHT_HQ: High quality noncanonical sub-genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
# nsgRPHT_LQ: Low quality noncanonical sub-genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
# nsgRPHT_LLQ: Low low quality noncanonical sub-genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
# nsgRPHT_All: All noncanonical sub-genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
